<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<bibRefCitation author="Bojer, W" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" refId="B16" refString="Bojer, W, 1837. Hortus Mauritianus. Aime Mararot &amp; Co., Mauritius, 1-456." title="Hortus Mauritianus. Aime Mararot &amp; Co., Mauritius, 1 - 456." year="1837">Bojer (1837)</bibRefCitation>
listed a plant from the Grand Bassin of Mauritius as 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Croton muricatus" order="Malpighiales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="muricatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Croton muricatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Vahl, a native Malagasy species. Based on this, the name &quot; 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. muricatus" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" rank="species" species="muricatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">C. muricatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bojer, nom. nud.&quot; has been included in several indices, including IPNI, Tropicos, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Govaerts, R" journalOrPublisher="Tropical Woods" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" refId="B24" refString="Govaerts, R, Frodin, DG, Radcliffe-Smith, A, 2000. World checklist and bibliography of Euphorbiaceae (and Pandanaceae), 4 vols. Royal Botanic Garden, Kew, UK, 1-1621." title="World checklist and bibliography of Euphorbiaceae (and Pandanaceae), 4 vols. Royal Botanic Garden, Kew, UK, 1 - 1621." year="2000">Govaerts et al. (2000)</bibRefCitation>
. In the same manner as 
<bibRefCitation author="Leandri, J" journalOrPublisher="Candollea" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" refId="B35" refString="Leandri, J, 1939. Les Croton de Madagascar et des iles voisines. Annales du Musee Colonial de Marseille, ser. 5, 7 (1): 1-100." title="Les Croton de Madagascar et des iles voisines. Annales du Musee Colonial de Marseille, ser. 5, 7 (1): 1 - 100." year="1939">Leandri (1939)</bibRefCitation>
, we interpret 
<bibRefCitation author="Bojer, W" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Botany" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" refId="B16" refString="Bojer, W, 1837. Hortus Mauritianus. Aime Mararot &amp; Co., Mauritius, 1-456." title="Hortus Mauritianus. Aime Mararot &amp; Co., Mauritius, 1 - 456." year="1837">Bojer (1837)</bibRefCitation>
as a misidentification of what 
<bibRefCitation author="Baillon, H" journalOrPublisher="Adansonia" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" pagination="139 - 173" refId="B3" refString="Baillon, H, 1861. Euphorbiacees Africaines. Deuxieme Partie, Afrique Orientale (Bourbon, Maurice, Madagascar, Zanguebar, etc.). Adansonia 1: 139 - 173" title="Euphorbiacees Africaines. Deuxieme Partie, Afrique Orientale (Bourbon, Maurice, Madagascar, Zanguebar, etc.)." volume="1" year="1861">Baillon (1861)</bibRefCitation>
later described as 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. fothergillifolius" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" rank="species" species="fothergillifolius">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">C. fothergillifolius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, rather than the publication of a nomen nudum.
</paragraph>
